# WPILib Agent Tools Core Rule

- Run code iteration in sandboxes, not directly in the workspace.
- Use `wpilib-agent-tools sandbox create --name <id> --source workspace` first.
- Execute iterative commands through `wpilib-agent-tools sandbox run --name <id> -- <command>`.
- Before proposing or applying robot-code changes, identify the current repo mode/switching pattern (simulation vs IRL, compile-time flags, runtime toggles).
- Check common mode locations first (for example `Constants.java`, mode enums, or sim/real selection logic) and align changes with the active pattern.
- Prefer `--json` for machine-consumable command output.
- Use `wpilib-agent-tools sandbox status` and `sandbox stop` to manage running jobs.
- Generate final changes with `wpilib-agent-tools sandbox patch --name <id> --output <file>`.
- After patch generation, clean completed sandboxes with `wpilib-agent-tools sandbox clean --name <id>` unless the user asks to keep them.
- Apply reviewed patch output to workspace only after explicit approval.
